Filipina superhero Wave comic launch, signing draws thousands of fans
A variant cover of the maiden issue of New Agents...
body:
05/12/19

Filipina superhero Wave comic launch, signing draws thousands of fans

  • A variant cover of the maiden issue of New Agents of Atlas that is tied in with the current War of the Realms event features the first-ever Filipino superhero in the Marvel Universe, Wave, as drawn by Pinoy comics illustrator Mico Suayan.
  • According to Sandy Sansolis, owner of local specialty shop Comic Odyssey, he ordered 4,000 copies of the Suayan-illustrated cover and during the Saturday, May 11, launch and signing with Suayan at the Robinsons Galleria, the title was close to selling out.

At age thirteen, Peter Parker has gone through much more tragedy than a kid should ever know. His parents died when he was young, he watched his uncle get murdered in front of him, his aunt was destroyed by cancer. After being placed in foster care, Peter starts digging into his ancestry when he starts questioning his appearance based on his parents genes. Things don’t make sense. Through hacking, DNA swatches, and sneaking around, Peter starts to unravel secrets that should have just stayed hidden.

summary: thoughts on Endgame? (if you'd like to share them, you're not obligated to, of course!)
question: thoughts on Endgame? (if you'd like to share them, you're not obligated to, of course!)
answer:
This not a spoiler free post!

So, I went to see it in the very first time it was screened in my general area, which was at about 7pm Greenwich Time of the Worldwide release day. So, pretty early. I loved it, and cried a lot too.

And then more and more people started seeing it and commenting on it, mostly about the end of Steve’s arc. At the beginning I didn’t really agree: I liked how they did it and thought those fans were speaking more from their hurt hearts than from their brains, which is completely understandable.

As time went on, I began changing my opinion (and I think that says a lot about Tumblr’s incredible opinion-changing power) and was almost convinced the end of Steve’s arc was actually BAD and WRONG.

But, just in time, I went to see it again in the Monday of the end of the spoiler ban, so about two weeks after it premiered. The end of Steve’s arc? I still love it and don’t think it’s unreasonable at all. Bucky knew what Steve was going to do and I’m not angry or sad about it.

Now, before you click off, you can scroll through my blog and you’ll see how much of a Stucky shipper I am. To me, it’s THAT ship. Hell, bucky’s my favorite mcu character! But I still think the character arc end was appropriate, even if Peggy was a little shoehorned into the start of the movie (aka ‘life of my life’) - but only at the start. Seeing Steve dressed as a military guy longing for her was pretty heartbreaking tbh and his decision at the end, to me, makes sense.

Feel free to comment on this post! Though I will NOT post a lot about this subject, as well as I’ll not allow hate to be thrown towards me for this. Let’s not make it civil war. 2?
